The students will  get knowledge about methods of health economics and health care management and about actual problems in those areas. Additionally the students will be introduced the concepts of entrepreneurship and marketing. Students are  dealing with specific economical problems in stomatology and their possible solutions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce main concepts of health economics, health care management, entrepreneurship and marketing and their application in dental care.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who successfully finish the course should: - analyse the structure and main terms of health economics; - understand and can use in practice basic knowledge in methods of economic assessments; - know main health care management principles and describe functions and goals of health care systems; - know organisation and legislation of Estonian public health and health care system; - understand basic concepts of entrepreneurship and marketing and application possibilities in dental care.
